> @sunmTree can you please give me a little bit more details on this?
> I am less familiar with the Reflection API.

Like this:

```
try {
            Class<?> lottieCacheClass = Class.forName("com.airbnb.lottie.model.LottieCompositionCache");
            Method instance = lottieCacheClass.getDeclaredMethod("getInstance");
            Method clearMethod = lottieCacheClass.getMethod("clear", null);
            clearMethod.invoke(instance.invoke(null, null));
        } catch (ClassNotFoundException | NoSuchMethodException
                | IllegalAccessException | InvocationTargetException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
```

[Using Java Reflection](https://www.oracle.com/technical-resources/articles/java/javareflection.html)

